### `RouteMatcher::findVirtualHost()` — L2251

Virtual host lookup against the `Host` / `:authority` header:

```
1. Fast path: if only default_virtual_host_ exists, return it immediately
2. Exact match: virtual_hosts_.find(host)  (hash map, O(1))
3. Wildcard suffix: findWildcardVirtualHost() with suffix substring
   - "foo-bar.baz.com" matches "*-bar.baz.com" before "*.baz.com"
   - Ordered by wildcard length descending (longest match wins)
4. Wildcard prefix: findWildcardVirtualHost() with prefix substring
5. Default virtual host (catch-all "*")
```

### `VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromEntries()` — L2116

```cpp
RouteConstSharedPtr VirtualHostImpl::getRouteFromEntries(...) const {
  // SSL redirect check
  if (ssl_requirements_ == SslRequirements::All && scheme != "https") {
    return ssl_redirect_route_;
  }

  if (matcher_) {
    // Unified matcher path: evaluate MatchTree<HttpMatchingData>
    Http::Matching::HttpMatchingDataImpl data(stream_info);
    data.onRequestHeaders(headers);
    auto match = Matcher::evaluateMatch<Http::HttpMatchingData>(*matcher_, data);
    if (match.result_) {
      return getRouteFromRoutes(cb, headers, stream_info, random_value, {route_action.route()});
    }
    return nullptr;
  }

  // Linear scan of routes_ list
  return getRouteFromRoutes(cb, headers, stream_info, random_value, routes_);
}
```

### `RouteEntryImplBase::matchRoute()` — L913

Each route entry's `matches()` method calls `matchRoute()` which checks all configured predicates:

```cpp
bool RouteEntryImplBase::matchRoute(const Http::RequestHeaderMap& headers,
                                    const StreamInfo::StreamInfo& stream_info,
                                    uint64_t random_value) const {
  bool matches = true;
  matches &= evaluateRuntimeMatch(random_value);   // runtime fraction
  matches &= Grpc::Common::isGrpcRequestHeaders(headers);  // if grpc_only
  matches &= Http::HeaderUtility::matchHeaders(headers, config_headers_);  // header matchers
  matches &= ConfigUtility::matchQueryParams(query_parameters, config_query_parameters_);
  matches &= evaluateTlsContextMatch(stream_info);  // TLS metadata
  matches &= m.match(stream_info.dynamicMetadata());  // dynamic metadata
  matches &= m->match(stream_info.filterState());     // filter state
  return matches;
}
```

