## 14. Key Data Structures and Interfaces

### Connection Lifecycle Objects

| Object | File | Role |
|--------|------|------|
| `TcpListenerImpl` | `network/tcp_listener_impl.cc` | Owns listener socket fd, libevent registration |
| `ActiveTcpListener` | `listener_manager/active_tcp_listener.cc` | Per-listener accept logic, connection balancing |
| `ActiveTcpSocket` | `listener_manager/active_tcp_socket.cc` | Listener filter chain state machine |
| `FilterChainManagerImpl` | `listener_manager/filter_chain_manager_impl.cc` | Multi-level filter chain trie |
| `ServerConnectionImpl` | `network/connection_impl.cc` | Downstream TCP connection |
| `ConnectionManagerImpl` | `http/conn_manager_impl.cc` | HTTP Connection Manager (HCM) |
| `ActiveStream` | `http/conn_manager_impl.cc` | Single HTTP stream state |
| `FilterManager` | `http/filter_manager.cc` | HTTP filter chain execution |
| `Router::Filter` | `router/router.cc` | Terminal decoder filter, upstream dispatch |
| `UpstreamRequest` | `router/upstream_request.cc` | Single upstream attempt |
| `ConnPoolImplBase` | `conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc` | Connection pool base |
| `ClientConnectionImpl` | `network/connection_impl.cc` | Upstream TCP connection |

### Critical Interfaces

| Interface | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|
| `Network::ReadFilter` | Implemented by HCM; receives raw bytes from network layer |
| `Network::ListenerFilter` | Implemented by TLS/HTTP inspectors; peeks connection metadata |
| `Http::StreamDecoderFilter` | Implemented by each HTTP decoder filter |
| `Http::StreamEncoderFilter` | Implemented by each HTTP encoder filter |
| `Upstream::LoadBalancer` | Implemented by RR, LR, Ring Hash, etc.; selects host |
| `ConnectionPool::Instance` | Implemented by HTTP/1, HTTP/2, HTTP/3 pools |
| `Network::TransportSocket` | Implemented by RawBuffer, TLS; wraps I/O |
| `GenericConnPool` | Router-facing pool abstraction (HTTP/TCP/UDP) |

### Thread-Local State

All hot-path data structures are thread-local to avoid locking:

| Structure | Location | Purpose |
|-----------|----------|---------|
| `ThreadLocalClusterManagerImpl` | `cluster_manager_impl.cc` | Per-worker cluster + pool maps |
| `host_http_conn_pool_map_` | `ThreadLocalClusterManagerImpl` | `host → ConnPoolsContainer` |
| `ConnPoolsContainer::pools_` | Per-host | `(priority, hash_key) → pool` |
| `priority_set_` | `ClusterEntry` | Thread-local host set snapshot |
| `lb_` | `ClusterEntry` | Thread-local LB instance |

xDS updates push new cluster/endpoint snapshots to each worker thread via the dispatcher's `post()` mechanism, replacing the thread-local snapshots atomically without locks.

